tip.text: A small tradition ramen place. Open til late night (2pm) Good miso soup with a hint of fresh ginger that makes the soup base flavor more tasty.
We have tried 3 of their ramen: 1. Miso = yummy with a buttery taste ; 2. Soy Sauce = if your not a fan of strong soup base, this is a good choice; 3. Salt base = luv the light and flavorable soup.
Fine dine french dinner and friendly staff. Must try their truffle risotto and lamp chop (super tender and juicy). If ur a fan of garlic, try their pink garlic soup too.
